frameDefinitions: This frame is concerned with the idea that people (Participant_1, Participant_2, or Participants) participate in an organized, rule-governed activity (the Competition) in order to achieve some advantageous outcome (often the Prize).
A Location is characterized by a high amount of (often goal-oriented) Activity, or metonymically, with Individuals who are engaged in the activity.
This frame covers the basic uses of direction words like the adverbs east, up, and forward.
A Lessee gains the use of Goods owned by a Lessor by payment to the Lessor.
This frame contains words for motions or actions an Agent performs using some part of his/her body.
A Theme moves with respect to a Fixed_location, generally with a certain Periodicity, without undergoing unbounded translational motion or significant alteration of configuration/shape.
frameExamples: We are <t>renting</t> our apartment from a kind man named Tom.
listRoleDefinitions: This role identifies the first (or only) participant in a competition.
This role identifies the second participant in a competition.
This role is used for plural NP participants in a competition.
This role is used for the name of the competition.
The period of time when the <fen>Competition</fen> occurs.

Where the event takes place. 
A constituent tagged as <fen>Place</fen> may require annotation on a secondary FE-layer.
The <fen>Location</fen> where a lot of activity is taking place, or prototypically takes place.
The <fen>Activity</fen> that is conceptually filling the <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Individuals</fen> are engaged in the <fen>Activity</fen>, creating a lively <fen>Location</fen>.
The <fen>Time</fen> during which the <fen>Location</fen> is characterized by a lot of activity.
The larger or general area where the <fen>Location</fen> is lively.
The one-dimensional set of locations.
The individual that gains temporary use of the <fen>Goods</fen> by paying the <fen>Lessor</fen>
The role <fen>Goods</fen> is an item which is temporarily exchanged for <fen>Money</fen> in a transaction.
When the event occurs.
The location the renting takes place.
The <fen>Agent</fen> uses some part of his/her body to perform the action. <fen>Agent</fen> occurs as the External Argument.

This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the body movement occurs.
The location within which the movement of a <fen>Body_part</fen> takes place.
A physical entity that is participating in non-translational motion.
The time at which the <fen>Theme</fen> is in bounded motion.
The location where the bounded motion happens.
